Supervised model training

지도 학습에 필요한 패키지 설치 및 불러오기

### library install
# install.packages('rpart')
# install.packages('rpart.plot')
# install.packages('adabag')
# install.packages('randomForest')
# install.packages('caret')
library(rpart)
library(rpart.plot)
library(adabag)

library(caret)

최소한의 입력값을 사용하여 모델링

### Default training
########################################################
#################### Tree 기반 모델 ####################
########################################################
### Decision Tree 
fit_tree <- rpart(class~.,data = train_df, method='class')
### Bagging Decision Tree
fit_bagging <- bagging(class~., data = train_df)
### Boosting Decision Tree
fit_boosting <- boosting(class~., data = train_df)
### randomforest
fit_rf <- randomForest(class~., data = train_df)

각 training의 accuracy는 confusionMatrix함수를 사용하거나 학습된 모델에서 바로 확인할 수 있다.

#### training accuracy

pred_tree<-predict(fit_tree,type='class')
pred_bagging <- predict(fit_bagging,newdata = train_df, type='class')
pred_boosting <- predict(fit_boosting,newdata = train_df, type='class')
pred_rf <- predict(fit_rf,type='class')

#####
### confusionMatrix(예측한 값, 실제값)
tree_accuracy <- confusionMatrix(pred_tree, train_df$class)[["overall"]][["Accuracy"]]
bagging_accuracy <- confusionMatrix(factor(pred_bagging$class), train_df$class)[["overall"]][["Accuracy"]]
boosting_accuracy <- confusionMatrix(factor(pred_boosting$class), train_df$class)[["overall"]][["Accuracy"]]
rf_accuracy <- confusionMatrix(pred_rf, train_df$class)[["overall"]][["Accuracy"]]
tree_accuracy ; bagging_accuracy ; boosting_accuracy ; rf_accuracy
## [1] 0.5651339
## [1] 0.6062093
## [1] 0.6191187
## [1] 0.7349835

Feature Importance

Tree 기반 모델을 사용하는 이유 중 feature importance를 확인할 수 있다.

feature importance의 값이 높을수록 그 변수가 중요하다.

### feature important
a <- data.frame('feature'=names(fit_tree$variable.importance),'tree_FI'=fit_tree$variable.importance)
b <- data.frame('feature'=names(fit_bagging$importance), 'bagging_FI'=fit_bagging$importance)
c <- data.frame('feature'=names(fit_boosting$importance), 'boosting_FI' = fit_boosting$importance)
d <- data.frame('feature'=rownames(fit_rf$importance), 'rf_FI' = as.numeric(fit_rf$importance))
ab <- merge(a,b,key='feature')
cd <- merge(c,d,key='feature')
abcd <- merge(ab,cd,key='feature')
abcd
##                    feature     tree_FI bagging_FI boosting_FI      rf_FI

#### 순위를 매겨 변수중요도를 확인해보자
abcd2 <- abcd
abcd2$tree_FI <- rank(-abcd$tree_FI)
abcd2$bagging_FI <- rank(-abcd$bagging_FI)
abcd2$boosting_FI <- rank(-abcd$boosting_FI)
abcd2$rf_FI <- rank(-abcd$rf_FI)

K-Nearest Neighbor classification

K개를 설정해야 되는 Model

K는 같은 class로 볼 데이터의 수이다.

K = HyperParameter(초모수)

### install.packages(caret)
library(caret)
fit_knn <- train(class~.,
                 data = train_df,
                 method = 'knn',
                 tuneLength = 4)
fit_knn
## k-Nearest Neighbors 
##

Support Vector Machine(SVM)

svm에서 사용되는 초모수는 C이다.

C가 작을수록 margin에서 오분류를 허용하며, C가 클수록 margin에서 오분류에서 허용을 하지 않는다.

fit_svm <- train(class~.,
                 data = train_df,
                 method = 'svmLinear',
                 tuneGrid = expand.grid(C = c(0.1,1,10)))

### 군집분석시 주의할점

거리기반 군집분석일 경우 단위에 굉장히 민감하다.

ex) a = (1,2,3,4,5)(단위:m), b = (100,200,300,400,500)(단위:cm)

같은 단위를 가지는 변수일 경우 상관이 없지만 다른 단위를 가지는 변수가 존재하는 경우

scaling을 통해 단위를 없애준다.

도메인을 활용하여 모델링 하기

bp_df$gender <- as.factor(bp_df$gender)
bp_df$class <- as.factor(bp_df$class)
bp_df_m <- bp_df[bp_df$gender == 'M',]
bp_df_f <- bp_df[bp_df$gender != 'M',]
bp_df_m <- bp_df_m[,-2]
bp_df_f <- bp_df_f[,-2]
train_m_size <- round(dim(bp_df_m)[1]*0.7)
train_f_size <- round(dim(bp_df_f)[1]*0.7)
set.seed(1004)
train_m_df_index <- sample(1:dim(bp_df_m)[1],train_m_size)
train_f_df_index <- sample(1:dim(bp_df_f)[1],train_f_size)

train_m_df <- bp_df_m[train_m_df_index,]
test_m_df <- bp_df_m[-train_m_df_index,]

train_f_df <- bp_df_f[train_f_df_index,]
test_f_df <- bp_df_f[-train_f_df_index,]
fit_train_m <- randomForest(class~.,data = train_m_df)
fit_train_f <- randomForest(class~.,data = train_f_df)
tr <- sum(diag(confusionMatrix(fit_train_m$predicted, train_m_df$class)[["table"]] + confusionMatrix(fit_train_f$predicted, train_f_df$class)[["table"]]))/ sum(confusionMatrix(fit_train_m$predicted, train_m_df$class)[["table"]] + confusionMatrix(fit_train_f$predicted, train_f_df$class)[["table"]])

######################################################################################################

te <- sum(diag(confusionMatrix(predict(fit_train_m,newdata=test_m_df,type='class'),test_m_df$class)[['table']] + confusionMatrix(predict(fit_train_f,newdata=test_f_df,type='class'),test_f_df$class)[['table']]))/ sum(confusionMatrix(predict(fit_train_m,newdata=test_m_df,type='class'),test_m_df$class)[['table']] + confusionMatrix(predict(fit_train_f,newdata=test_f_df,type='class'),test_f_df$class)[['table']])


train_test_accuracy_df3 <-data.frame('train_accuracy'= c(tr),
           'test_accuracy' = c(te),
           row.names = c('domain_rf'))
train_test_accuracy_df3
